<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1981] Not all PHP libraries are installed when building an installing a debian package</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1981</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When building and installing a php library Debian package not all the library files get installed. When trying to create a thrift client it has dependencies on these files but they don&apos;t exist. I tried to see if this issue was already logged in Jira but was unable to locate. If this is a duplicate please accept my apologies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve fixed this by adding the appropriate files to the Makefile.am and have tested this on my system and it seems to work as I&apos;d expect. I wasn&apos;t quite sure how to get this change pushed back to the official git repo because I don&apos;t have committer access and the instructions for obtaining such access seem out of date (they are for SVN). That being the case I will create a for on the Github repo, commit my change and then create a pull request. If that is not acceptable please let me know the preferred way to submit a patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux / Debian / Ubuntu&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
